description._content: Birdseye view of crowds flanking procession of motor vehicles at centenary celebrations of first European crossing of Blue Mountains at Mount York in 1913. In centre of crowd, dignitaries stand in front of commemorative tablet, on platform with British, Australian and American flags. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains - Monuments and Celebrations', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
